%N A393336 a(n) is the sum of positions of 1's minus sum of positions of 0's in the binary expansion of n.
%C A393336 A weighted variant of A037861.
%C A393336 Position 1 corresponds to the least significant bit of n.
%C A393336 Conjecture: the sequence contains all integers.
%C A393336 Above conjecture is true. All positive integers are attained when n in binary is of the form 101010...10. All nonpositive integers are attained when n in binary is of the form 1001010101..01. - _Chai Wah Wu_, Feb 27 2026
%H A393336 Ruud H.G. van Tol, <a href="/A393336/b393336.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..10000</a>
%F A393336 a(n) = A029931(n) - A359400(n).
%F A393336 a(n) = A029931(n) - A029931(A035327(n)).
%F A393336 a(n) = 2*A029931(n)-A070939(n)*(A070939(n)+1)/2. - _Chai Wah Wu_, Feb 26 2026
%e A393336 a(6) = 4, because 6 = 110_2, and -1+2+3 = 4.
%e A393336 a(8) = -2, because 8 = 1000_2, and -1-2-3+4 = -2.
%p A393336 a:= n-> (l-> add(`if`(l[i]=0, -i, i), i=1..nops(l)))(convert(n, base, 2)):
%p A393336 seq(a(n), n=0..74);  # _Alois P. Heinz_, Feb 26 2026
%t A393336 A393336[n_] := Total[#*Range[Length[#], 1, -1]] & [2*IntegerDigits[n, 2] - 1];
%t A393336 Array[A393336, 100, 0] (* _Paolo Xausa_, Feb 26 2026 *)
%o A393336 (PARI) a(n)= my(d=Vecrev([ b-!b |b<-if(n, binary(n), [0])])); d*[1..#d]~
%o A393336 (PARI) a(n)= my(d=binary(n)); 2*d*-[-#d..-1]~ - binomial(#d+1, 2) - !n \\ _Ruud H.G. van Tol_, Feb 27 2026
